    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR5c0139-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_013-017cs.5.7.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2022-12-01T13:12:16.99+09:00">ZZJS 379 reads 獊 for 傖 and X for </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Wandering through the Great Void,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">I roam in the court of vagueness and uncertainty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Even greedy people</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and impatient scholars,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">if they but briefly grasp its lingering fragrance,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">taste its overflowing stream,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and perceive its faint sounds and shadows, are still enough to have a vast and unconstrained mind, forgetting themselves and finding contentment.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">How much more so for those who delve into its profound essence and contemplate its eternal nature!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Thus, they extend limitlessly into purity and remoteness, depart from the dust of the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and return to the ultimate darkness.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ps.3.18.1.9.4.3.9.1.3.2.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Preface to the Commentary on the True Scripture of Nanhua</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-002ss" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Composed by the Tang Dynasty's Master Cheng Xuanying of Xihua</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Zhuangzi is that which expounds the deep roots of Dao and Virtue,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">describes the subtle meaning of profound mystery,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">expresses the tranquility of non-action,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">illuminates the profound obscurity of solitary transformation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">restrains and silences the nine streams of thought,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and encompasses the hundred schools of philosophy.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">Truly, it is the supreme teaching within the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and in reality, the subtle words beyond phenomena.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">This man's surname was Zhuang, his given name Zhou,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">his style name Zixiu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">He was born in the Meng district of Suiyang in the state of Song.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">He took the noble Master Sang as his teacher,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">and received the title of Nanhua Immortal.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">He lived at the beginning of the Warring States period,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">nearing the end of the declining Zhou dynasty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:19:22.308+09:00">He lamented the insignificance of the lives of the people</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Lamenting the decline of morality,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">I was moved to passionate indignation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">and thus composed this treatise.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Its words are grand and extensive,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">its meaning profound and far-reaching,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">not to be heard by inferior men,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">how could shallow understanding fathom it!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Zi" as spoken of here,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">is an esteemed appellation for those of virtue.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">In ancient times, teachers were called "Zi,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">also "Zi" is said to be the name of a book.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">It is not only a general name for these three chapters,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">but also a common title for the various schools of thought.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Nei Pian" as spoken of here,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">establishes its name by taking the "inner" as the foundation for dealing with the "outer,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Pian" signifies the meaning of arranged tablets.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">In ancient times, green bamboo was scraped to make tablets,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">and leather was used for binding.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Arranged tablets become a "Pian,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">just as today, joined paper becomes a scroll.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Therefore, Yuan Kai said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Important matters are recorded on bamboo slips,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">minor matters are merely written on tablets."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Inner" then, discusses fundamental principles,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">"Outer" narrates historical events.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Although events are clearly evident,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">they cannot be understood without principles;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">although principles are subtle and profound,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">they cannot be revealed without events.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Desiring to first clarify the subtle principles,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">therefore, I have prominently labeled the "Inner Chapters" first.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">The principles of the "Inner Chapters" are profound,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.14.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">therefore, for each, I have separately established chapter headings outside the text.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR5c0139_tls_000-003cs.9.1.14.10.14.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-04-25T11:20:56.177+09:00">Guo Xiang still annotates immediately under the title,</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
